    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Houses having one rows of rooms in the floor plan, typically allowing access to rooms only through other rooms rather than via a corridor. Single-pile houses may have one or two stories.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050958/Oxford Dictionary of Architecture and Landscape Architecture (2000)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Huizen met één rij kamers in het grondplan, waarbij de kamers gewoonlijk alleen toegankelijk zijn vanuit andere kamers en niet vanuit een gang. Dit soort huizen heeft één of twee verdiepingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>樓面規劃有一排房間的房舍，通常進出房間不使用走廊，而是藉由其他房間出入。該類型房舍可能為一層樓或兩層樓建築。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
